Format Signature
For identifying whether the file is in the logger format, a signature is attached to the first 13 bytes of the file. This is based on the PNG file format.Â The first byte is non-ASCII to avoid text editors from opening it.
The following bytes are "B'ENERGY" in ASCII to identify this is our format.
The last four bytes are tests for improper text handling.
